    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-26T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="613"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d613">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–2654: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-26T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 26, 1954—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 313. Repeated information Paris 340,
                    Saigon 119. Re <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss>s 261<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d613fn1">Telegram <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 261, May
                        20, contained a report of a conversation between Under Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_NDL1">Ngo
                            Dinh Luyen</persName> on May 18. For memorandum of conversation, see
                            <ref target="#pg_843">p. 843</ref>.</note> and 265.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d613fn2">Dated May 20, <ref target="#pg_863">p. 863</ref>.</note>
                    Member <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> today told <persName
                        corresp="#p_NDL1">Ngo Dinh Luyen</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao
                        Dai</persName>’s personal emissary, that General <persName corresp="#p_SWB1"
                        >Smith</persName> has no comment for present <pb facs="0963" n="937"
                        xml:id="pg_937"/> regarding various questions as to US action in certain
                    contingencies (question referred mainly to US intervention if French pull out,
                    to US direct assistance for Vietnamese Army and US views on political
                    developments in Vietnam including particularly <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao
                        Dai</persName>’s alleged project of replacing <persName corresp="#p_BLP1"
                        >Buu Loc</persName> with <persName corresp="#p_NDD1">Ngo Dinh
                        Diem</persName>).</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NDL1">Ngo Dinh Luyen</persName> was told Under Secretary
                    appreciates contact established and that in addition Under Secretary believes,
                    if <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> concurs, that further meeting
                    between <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> and Under Secretary might
                    be useful in event <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> plans to be in
                    Geneva neighborhood. Date of such meeting tentatively suggested as late next
                    week after forthcoming French Assembly debate.</p>
                <p>We have endeavored impress <persName corresp="#p_NDL1">Ngo Dinh Luyen</persName>
                    with <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> view that (<hi rend="italic"
                    >a</hi>) nothing should be done to weaken French determination to react
                    vigorously in present military emergency in Tonkin and (<hi rend="italic"
                    >b</hi>) major importance that all positive elements on free world side
                    (including <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName>) should be united and
                    move forward in most coordinated fashion possible.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NDL1">Ngo Dinh Luyen</persName> tells us decision as to
                        <persName corresp="#p_NDD1">Ngo Dinh Diem</persName>’s departure for Saigon
                    not yet firm.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
